buster-cut
Homonym Number:  1
Word Class: noun
Sense Number:
Definition:a boyish close crop (? fashionable in late 1920s) (perhaps from prec. buster `boy, fellow'; <i>buster-cut</i>: (hair) `cut like a boy's').


